<item>
            <title>[LU-18996] Race condition when trying to list and unregister_device at same time</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18996</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
11452.499351] LustreError: 31833:0:(genops.c:658:class_num2obd()) ASSERTION( obd-&amp;gt;obd_minor == num ) failed: 00000000077de5fe obd_minor -1 != 142
[11452.501305] LustreError: 31833:0:(genops.c:658:class_num2obd()) LBUG
[11452.502282] CPU: 2 PID: 31833 Comm: lctl Kdump: loaded Tainted: P           OE     5.10.234-225.917.amzn2.aarch64 #1
[11452.503915] Hardware name: Amazon EC2 c6gn.8xlarge/, BIOS 1.0 11/1/2018
[11452.504951] Call trace:
[11452.505349]  dump_backtrace+0x0/0x204
[11452.505930]  show_stack+0x1c/0x24
[11452.506462]  dump_stack+0xe4/0x12c
[11452.507019]  lbug_with_loc+0x4c/0x80 [libcfs]
[11452.507746]  get_order+0x0/0x20 [obdclass]
[11452.508427]  obd_device_list_seq_show+0x24/0xfc [obdclass]
[11452.509288]  seq_read_iter+0x3c4/0x4c8
[11452.509887]  seq_read+0xe4/0x13c
[11452.510407]  full_proxy_read+0x64/0xb4
[11452.511005]  vfs_read+0xb0/0x1e8
[11452.511520]  ksys_read+0x70/0xfc
[11452.512037]  __arm64_sys_read+0x20/0x28
[11452.512646]  el0_svc_common.constprop.0+0x84/0x240
[11452.513394]  do_el0_svc+0x28/0x80
[11452.513920]  el0_svc+0x1c/0x28
[11452.514408]  el0_sync_handler+0x94/0x120
[11452.515069] Kernel panic - not syncing: LBUG &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When calling &lt;b&gt;&lt;tt&gt;obd_device_list_seq_show&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/b&gt;, if a &lt;b&gt;&lt;tt&gt;class_unregister_device&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/b&gt; is happening at same time, the race condition can cause issue where it trying to assert obd_minor == -1. In this case no need to &lt;b&gt;LBUG&lt;/b&gt;, just return NULL and behave like the obd device does not exist.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
